Package member

Class MemberDatabase

java.lang.Object
member.MemberDatabase
public class MemberDatabase extends Object
This class defines the Member Database using a single one dimensional array. That array will store all the added members to the database.
Author:
Hasnain Ali, Carolette Saguil

  • Constructor Details

    • MemberDatabase

      public MemberDatabase()
      Instantiates an empty Member Database where it's size is 0. Instantiates a member array of default array size of 4 that will store members added to the database and later grow as needed.

  • Method Details

    • find

      public int find(String firstName, String lastName, Date dob)
      Looks for member in the member database using member's first name, last name, and date of birth.
      Parameters:
      firstName - Member's firstName.
      lastName - Member's lastName.
      dob - Member's date of birth.
      Returns:
      index of the member in the member database, -1 otherwise.

    • find

      public int find(Member member)
      Looks for a Member in the member database.
      Parameters:
      member - Member to find the database index for.
      Returns:
      index of the member in the member database, -1 otherwise.

    • getMember

      public Member getMember(int index)
      Parameters:
      index - Index of member in the member database.
      Returns:
      Returns member at that index in the member database, null if index is invalid / is not in the database.

    • grow

      public void grow()
      Grows the member database when the current database is full. Size limited by JVM memory allocation. (How big Java will let you make an array before you run out of space).

    • add

      public boolean add(Member member)
      Adds member given to the member database. Returns false if member is already in the member database.
      Parameters:
      member - Member to be added.
      Returns:
      true if member was added, false otherwise.

    • remove

      public boolean remove(Member member)
      Removes member given from the member database. Returns false if member is not in the member database.
      Parameters:
      member - Member to be removed.
      Returns:
      true if member was removed, false otherwise.

    • print

      public void print()
      Prints out all members in the member database with no sorting.

    • printByCounty

      public void printByCounty()
      Prints out all the members in the member database, sorted by county then zipcode.

    • printByExpirationDate

      public void printByExpirationDate()
      Prints out all the members in the member database, sorted by expiration date.

    • printByName

      public void printByName()
      Prints out all the members in the member database, sorted by last name then first name.
